THIRD-PARTY ASSESSMENT FRAMEWORKS

The assessment instruments implemented in this pipeline are based on
published frameworks and are subject to their own licensing terms:

  - LUCAS (Liverpool Undergraduate Communication Assessment Scale):
    Developed by the University of Liverpool. Contact UoL for licensing
    terms. The instrument definitions in this repository are adapted for
    automated scoring research and do not constitute the original scale.

  - SPIKES Protocol:
    Published in Baile et al. (2000), The Oncologist 5(4), 302-311.
    Used under academic fair use for research purposes.

  - Informed Consent Structure (GSLP):
    Based on requirements defined in Section 630e of the German Civil Code
    (Buergerliches Gesetzbuch). Legal text is in the public domain.

  - Lumbar Puncture Informed Consent — Clinical Quality:
    Clinical quality rubric for informed consent conversations, derived from
    Section 630e BGB requirements and clinical best practice for lumbar
    puncture procedures. Developed for this project.

  - T1DM Diagnosis Disclosure — Clinical Content:
    Clinical content checklist for Type 1 Diabetes diagnosis disclosure,
    based on the S3-Leitlinie "Diagnostik, Therapie und Verlaufskontrolle
    des Diabetes mellitus im Kindes- und Jugendalter" (AWMF 057-016,
    Version 4.0, 2023) by the Deutsche Diabetes Gesellschaft (DDG).
    https://register.awmf.org/de/leitlinien/detail/057-016

These instrument definitions are provided for research reproducibility
only. Redistribution of the instrument definitions separately from this
pipeline may require separate permissions from the respective rights holders.

